A Markovian SIR epidemic is defined on the network of N individuals as follows. Each individual is at any point in time either susceptible, infective or recovered (and immune to further infection). An infective individual infects each of its susceptible neighbours at the points of independent Poisson processes, each having rate \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
