				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\gamma $$\end{document}γ, keeping all, if any, of its unpaired stubs. Note that in the formulation in Ball and Neal (2008), when an infective recovers, its unpaired stubs, if any, are paired immediately; however, that is not necessary and indeed complicates analysis of the model.

